<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1437,1636,2023]" lastBlockId="53.[151,1437,152,287]" lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1997,2023]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lyman" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[323,538,1996,2022]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="ljungmani">
<emphasis box="[323,538,1996,2022]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Ophiura ljungmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reported from the Azorean waters under three different names: 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="$ Lyman" authorityYear="1878" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" order="Ophiurida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="lepida">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Ophioglypha lepida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lyman" box="[268,423,153,179]" firstAuthor="Lyman" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="65 - 168" refId="ref188425" refString="Lyman, T. (1878) Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae of the &quot; Challenger &quot; expedition. Part I. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zo ˆ logy at Harvard College, 5 (7), 65 - 168." type="journal article" year="1878">Lyman (1878</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lyman" box="[438,497,153,179]" firstAuthor="Lyman" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 386" refId="ref188509" refString="Lyman, T. (1882) Report on the Ophiuroidea. Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H. M. S. Challenger 1873 - 1876, Zoology, 5 (14), 1 - 386." type="journal article" year="1882">1882</bibRefCitation>
; H.M.S. 
<emphasis box="[603,729,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Challenger</emphasis>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1878" box="[755,1038,152,178]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="ljungmanni">
<emphasis box="[755,1038,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Ophioglypha ljungmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1895" box="[1098,1340,152,178]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="thouleti">
<emphasis box="[1098,1340,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Ophioglypha thouleti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both by 
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler" box="[151,317,188,215]" firstAuthor="Koehler" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 317" refId="ref185837" refString="Koehler, R. (1909) Echinodermes provenant des campagnes du yacht Princesse-Alice (Asteries, Ophiures, Echinides et Crinoides). Resultats des campagnes scientifiques accomplies sur son yacht par Albert Ier Prince Souverain de Monaco, 34, 1 - 317." type="journal article" year="1909">Koehler (1909</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler" box="[329,401,189,215]" firstAuthor="Koehler" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref185986" refString="Koehler, R. (1921 a) Echinodermes (Asteries, Ophiures, Echinides et Crinoides) des dernieres campagnes de la Princesse-Alice et de l' Hirondelle II. Bulletin de l'Institut Oceanographique de Monaco, 396, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1921" yearSuffix="a">1921a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<emphasis box="[413,588,188,214]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Princesse Alice</emphasis>
). Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler" box="[684,869,188,215]" firstAuthor="Koehler" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 173" refId="ref185883" refString="Koehler, R. (1914 a) A Contribution to the Study of Ophiurans of the United States National Museum. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 84, 1 - 173. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.84.1" type="journal article" year="1914" yearSuffix="a">Koehler (1914a)</bibRefCitation>
found O. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1895" box="[985,1071,188,214]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="thouleti">
<emphasis box="[985,1071,188,214]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">thouleti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be identical with Lyman’s 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1878" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="ljungmanni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">O. ljungmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In turn, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mortensen" box="[382,596,225,251]" firstAuthor="Mortensen" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 121" refId="ref192677" refString="Mortensen, T. (1933 a) Ophiuroidea. The Danish Ingolf Expedition, 4 b (8), 1 - 121." type="journal article" year="1933" yearSuffix="a">Mortensen (1933a)</bibRefCitation>
found the diagnosing characters that separate 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="$ Lyman" authorityYear="1878" box="[1115,1220,224,251]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="lepida">
<emphasis box="[1115,1220,224,251]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">O. lepida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lyman" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[1288,1437,224,251]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="ljungmani">
<emphasis box="[1288,1437,224,251]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">O. ljungmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mostly size related and established the synonymy.
</paragraph>
